Package com.yardi.shared.QSECOFR

Class EditUserProfileRequest

java.lang.Object
com.yardi.shared.QSECOFR.EditUserProfileRequest
public class EditUserProfileRequest extends Object
Java representation of the web request to edit the user profile and the response to that request.

The web request comes in as JSON and gets mapped to this class to make it easier to work with the request. When responding to the request, select fields are mapped to JSON to become the response. Fields annotated @JsonIgnore are not mapped in either the request or the response.

    • EditUserProfileRequest

      public EditUserProfileRequest(String action, String findUser, String msgID, String msgDescription, String firstName, String lastName, String address1, String address2, String city, String state, String zip, String zip4, String phone, String fax, String email, String ssn, String dob, String homeMarket, String activeYN, String pwdExpDate, String disabledDate, String disabledTime, String pwdAttempts, String currentToken, String lastLogin, String lastLoginTime)
      Constructor used when responding to the web request.

      All parms set fields used for presentation purposes. To respond to the web request, values from Full_User_Profile entity are mapped to the parms of this constructor which will set fields of the same name. The fields having the same name as these parms are then mapped to JSON before responding.

      Parameters:
      action - the requested type of edit
      findUser - ID of the user profile to edit
      msgID - message ID
      msgDescription - message description
      firstName - user profile first name
      lastName - user profile last name
      address1 - user profile address line 1
      address2 - user profile address line 2
      city - user profile city
      state - user profile state
      zip - user profile zip
      zip4 - user profile zip4
      phone - user profile phone number
      fax - user profile fax number
      email - user profile email address
      ssn - user profile ssn
      dob - user profile birth date
      homeMarket - user profile home market
      activeYN - indicates whether user profile is active. Y is active. N is inactive
      pwdExpDate - user profile password expiration date. Password must be changed on or after this date.
      disabledDate - date on which the user profile was disabled due to too many invalid password attempts since the most recent successful login
      disabledTime - time when the user profile was disabled due to too many invalid password attempts since the most recent successful login
      pwdAttempts - number of invalid password attempts since the most recent successful login
      currentToken - hashed password
      lastLogin - date of the most recent successful login
      lastLoginTime - time of the most recent successful login

    • setProfileDisabledDate

      public void setProfileDisabledDate(Date profileDisabledDate)
      Set the date and time when the profile was disabled due to too many invalid password attempts since most recent successful login.

      A GregorianCalendar constructed from the century, year, month and day components of field disabledDate. The GregorianCalendar time is set to the hour, minute and second components of field disabledTime. Parm profileDisabledDate gets its value from the GregorianCalendar mills.

      Parameters:
      profileDisabledDate - date and time when the profile was disabled

    • stringify

      public String[] stringify(Timestamp date)
      Convert the given Timestamp to a date String and a time String for presentation purposes.

      Date String is in MM/DD/CCYY format. Time String is in hh:mm:ss format.

      Parameters:
      date - the Timestamp to convert.
      Returns:
      String [] containing the string representation of the date and time components of the given Timestamp. Element zero is the date String. Element one is the time String.

    • toDate

      public Date toDate(String dateString, String timeString, boolean withTime)
      Convert the given Strings to a Date with an optional time component.

      Note that it is unnecessary to return a Timestamp since the mills of the returned date can be used to construct a new Timestamp.

      Parameters:
      dateString - String representation of a date in MM/DD/CCYY format
      timeString - String representation of a time in hh:mm:ss format.
      withTime - boolean that indicates that the returned Date will have a time component.
      Returns:
      Date with an optional time component
